Step 1: Identify the liquid (quick) assets as the sum of:
 • Cash on Hand (End_amount) = -206636.07  
 • Bank Deposits (End_amount) = 2406.99  
 • Interest Receivable (End_amount) = 1225.71  
 • Accounts Receivable (End_amount) = 1604015.21

Step 2: Sum the quick assets:
 Quick assets = (-206636.07) + 2406.99 + 1225.71 + 1604015.21  
  = (-206636.07 + 2406.99) + 1225.71 + 1604015.21  
  = (-204229.08) + 1225.71 + 1604015.21  
  = (-203003.37) + 1604015.21  
  = 1401011.84

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities from the balance sheet:
 Total Current Liabilities (End_amount) = 737762.05

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 1401011.84 / 737762.05  
  ≈ 1.90

Thus, the Quick Ratio is approximately 1.90.
